    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mahogany having a pattern of curly, flamed, or tiger-striped marks, resembling the pattern seen in wood of violins, which are actually made of various woods other than mahogany.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
